Cristiano Ronaldo made 438 appearances for the Spanish club giants, scoring a staggering 450 goals in his nine years in Spain. JOHANNESBURG - Portugal Captain Cristiano Ronaldo has signed a 4-year contract with Serie A champions Juventus from Real Madrid for a reported fee of 100 million Euros. Ronaldo made 438 appearances for the Spanish club giants, scoring a staggering 450 goals in his nine years in Spain. During his tenure at Madrid, Ronaldo won two LaLiga titles, two Cop del Rey titles, two Spanish Super Cups, four Champions Leagues, two Eufa Super Cups and three Club World Cup titles for an impressive tally of 15 titles in Spain.  